Let:

$A$ represents Jam Corporation, and;

$B$ represents Pearl Inc.

Now, In our task, we have that Jam Corporation is willing to acquire Pearl Inc. for $\$228$ million when its market value is only $\$214$ million.

This offer would only make sense for Jam Corporation ***if the resulting benefit of the combination of two firms is greater than the sum of the market value of each company**: 

$$
\begin{equation}
V_{AB}>V_{A}+V_{B_{\text{Market}}}
\end{equation}
$$
Where:
$V_{B_{\text{Market}}}$ is the market value of the firm $B$.
